"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-12-05-paris-olympics-followed-ever-ioc\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"LAUSANNE,\\u00a0Switzerland\\u00a0(AFP)-\\u00a0The Paris Olympics were the most followed Games in television and social media history, the International Olympic Committee (IOC) said Thursday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999976250031531, \"rank\": 1.4381146577365296e-06, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 121, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 121, \"end\": 158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic Games Paris 2024 were the most followed Olympic Games ever,\\\" IOC president Thomas Bach told reporters at the end of an executive board meeting in Lausanne.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 249, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.18169498079e-15, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"score\": 0.999999025441659, \"rank\": 8.623200641000186e-07, \"text\": \"Lausanne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lausanne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"84 per cent of the potential audience - that means around 5 billion people around the globe - followed these Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bach added: \\\"Every viewer watched, on average, nine hours of coverage, a 20 per cent increase on the previous Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.999999678779938, \"rank\": 3.2122019361384666e-07, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the home market of France, 95 per cent of the potential audience watched an average of 24 hours of coverage of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9969812901405785, \"rank\": 0.0024845273051572747, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Engagement with the Olympic Games Paris 2024 on social media went, literally, through the roof,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.999999678779938, \"rank\": 3.2122019361384666e-07, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There were 412 billion engagements, an incredible 290 per cent increase on the previous edition of the Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bach said that Paris 2024 had \\\"demonstrated the unprecedented global appeal of the Olympic Games\\\".\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 1041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.999999678779938, \"rank\": 3.2122019361384666e-07, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1171072813642406e-15, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Audiences are following and interacting with the Olympic Games like never before.\\\"\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The independent surveys also demonstrate that people believe that the Olympic Movement's mission to unite the world in peaceful competition is more important than ever in a divided world; and that the Olympic values truly resonate with younger generations.\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1199, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999982808211597, \"rank\": 1.719181685645206e-06, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These were Olympic Games of a new era.\\\"\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The brand tracker, broadcast research, and consumer and athlete surveys\\u00a0were conducted by Nielsen, Ipsos and Publicis Sport & Entertainment.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1519, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Corporation\", \"score\": 0.5930871132766691, \"rank\": 0.4881139647098511, \"text\": \"Nielsen\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Corporation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nielsen_Corporation\"}, {\"begin\": 1528, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ipsos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.347198414693905e-15, \"text\": \"Ipsos\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ipsos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ipsos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across all consumer studies a total of more than 55,000 people in 18 countries were surveyed, with all respondents aged between 13 and 65, according to the IOC.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.18169498079e-15, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": []}]}"